						               													<description>From the website:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Pulp Alley captures the fast-paced excitement of classic cliffhanger serials and pulp magazines to more modern action/adventure stories. Designed primarily as a multi-player miniatures game, each Pulp Alley scenario is jammed full of villains, unexpected perils, and plenty of two-fisted action.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Pulp Alley&amp;rsquo;s unique and innovative rules offer players a thrill-packed and engaging experience &amp;ndash;&amp;#10;&amp;bull; Pulp Alley plays at the pulse-pounding pace of your favorite pulps and serials.&amp;#10;&amp;bull; Characters are easy to create and customize, making each league unique.&amp;#10;&amp;bull; Players never need to consult charts during a scenario. The action is on the tabletop &amp;ndash; not in a rulebook.&amp;#10;&amp;bull; Control of the Initiative is based on events as they occur during the scenario rather than an arbitrary die-roll.&amp;#10;&amp;bull; Fights are fast-paced and simultaneously dangerous for both characters, instead of the old I-shoot-then-you-shoot sequence.&amp;#10;&amp;bull; Perils and challenges are unpredictable and offer multiple paths to success.&amp;#10;&amp;bull; Scenarios are plot-driven, encouraging action, and offering an array of different rewards.&amp;#10;&amp;bull; Through campaigns and experience your characters can increase their skills and develop new abilities.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
